[{"text": "hello everyone welcome to IGCSE study", "start": 0.179, "duration": 5.64}, {"text": "buddy where you can revise biology", "start": 3.54, "duration": 6.599}, {"text": "topics from the Cambridge IGCSE syllabus", "start": 5.819, "duration": 6.961}, {"text": "if you are enjoying these videos so far", "start": 10.139, "duration": 4.741}, {"text": "please don't forget to hit the like", "start": 12.78, "duration": 6.56}, {"text": "button and subscribe to our Channel", "start": 14.88, "duration": 4.46}, {"text": "in this video you are going to learn", "start": 19.92, "duration": 5.3}, {"text": "part 2 of chapter 21", "start": 22.38, "duration": 8.04}, {"text": "biotechnology and genetic modification", "start": 25.22, "duration": 8.98}, {"text": "genetic modification is changing the DNA", "start": 30.42, "duration": 7.08}, {"text": "of living things like plants or animals", "start": 34.2, "duration": 6.96}, {"text": "to make them have specific traits or do", "start": 37.5, "duration": 6.44}, {"text": "certain things", "start": 41.16, "duration": 2.78}, {"text": "genetic modification is changing the", "start": 45.239, "duration": 6.541}, {"text": "genetic material of an organism by", "start": 48.36, "duration": 5.16}, {"text": "removing", "start": 51.78, "duration": 8.0}, {"text": "changing or inserting individual genes", "start": 53.52, "duration": 6.26}, {"text": "let's now learn the process of genetic", "start": 60.42, "duration": 6.18}, {"text": "modification let's use the bacterial", "start": 63.539, "duration": 6.061}, {"text": "production of a human protein as an", "start": 66.6, "duration": 5.94}, {"text": "example so let's say we want to make the", "start": 69.6, "duration": 5.46}, {"text": "human protein insulin", "start": 72.54, "duration": 5.34}, {"text": "the first part of the process is the", "start": 75.06, "duration": 5.879}, {"text": "isolation of the human gene", "start": 77.88, "duration": 5.82}, {"text": "the particular human gene in this case", "start": 80.939, "duration": 5.881}, {"text": "the gene for insulin is cut from its", "start": 83.7, "duration": 6.9}, {"text": "original DNA source", "start": 86.82, "duration": 7.02}, {"text": "restriction enzymes are used to cut the", "start": 90.6, "duration": 4.86}, {"text": "gene", "start": 93.84, "duration": 4.319}, {"text": "restriction enzymes are like tiny", "start": 95.46, "duration": 6.9}, {"text": "scissors for DNA they cut DNA at", "start": 98.159, "duration": 7.401}, {"text": "specific spots", "start": 102.36, "duration": 3.2}, {"text": "please note that the scissor image has", "start": 107.159, "duration": 4.981}, {"text": "been added only for illustrative", "start": 110.1, "duration": 4.86}, {"text": "purposes to symbolize restriction", "start": 112.14, "duration": 4.68}, {"text": "enzymes", "start": 114.96, "duration": 5.46}, {"text": "this action results in pieces having", "start": 116.82, "duration": 6.799}, {"text": "sticky ends", "start": 120.42, "duration": 3.199}, {"text": "next cutting bacterial plasmid", "start": 127.799, "duration": 7.08}, {"text": "use the same restriction enzymes to cut", "start": 131.459, "duration": 7.441}, {"text": "the bacterial plasmid DNA", "start": 134.879, "duration": 6.901}, {"text": "this results in complementary sticky", "start": 138.9, "duration": 5.12}, {"text": "ends", "start": 141.78, "duration": 6.42}, {"text": "plasmids are circles of DNA found inside", "start": 144.02, "duration": 7.74}, {"text": "bacterial cells", "start": 148.2, "duration": 3.56}, {"text": "formation of recombinant plasmid", "start": 161.0, "duration": 7.48}, {"text": "join the human gene piece with the cut", "start": 165.36, "duration": 8.7}, {"text": "plasmid DNA using DNA ligase", "start": 168.48, "duration": 9.78}, {"text": "ligase enzymes work like glue they paste", "start": 174.06, "duration": 8.0}, {"text": "the pieces of DNA together", "start": 178.26, "duration": 3.8}, {"text": "this creates a recombinant plasmid", "start": 182.22, "duration": 5.12}, {"text": "please note that the glue image has been", "start": 188.34, "duration": 7.02}, {"text": "added only for illustrative purposes to", "start": 191.7, "duration": 7.64}, {"text": "symbolize ligase enzymes", "start": 195.36, "duration": 7.26}, {"text": "insertion into bacteria", "start": 199.34, "duration": 6.7}, {"text": "insert the recombinant plasmid into", "start": 202.62, "duration": 6.72}, {"text": "bacteria enabling them to carry the", "start": 206.04, "duration": 7.1}, {"text": "modified genetic material", "start": 209.34, "duration": 3.8}, {"text": "bacterial multiplication", "start": 220.159, "duration": 6.101}, {"text": "allow the bacteria containing", "start": 223.5, "duration": 5.94}, {"text": "recombinant plasmids to multiply", "start": 226.26, "duration": 6.24}, {"text": "this increases the modified genetic", "start": 229.44, "duration": 5.659}, {"text": "material", "start": 232.5, "duration": 2.599}, {"text": "finally protein expression the bacteria", "start": 243.12, "duration": 7.619}, {"text": "use the inserted human gene to create", "start": 247.26, "duration": 6.42}, {"text": "the human protein insulin in this", "start": 250.739, "duration": 6.421}, {"text": "example a process known as protein", "start": 253.68, "duration": 6.26}, {"text": "expression", "start": 257.16, "duration": 2.78}, {"text": "here are a few situations where genetic", "start": 265.44, "duration": 6.84}, {"text": "modification might be applied", "start": 268.62, "duration": 6.42}, {"text": "the insertion of human genes into", "start": 272.28, "duration": 6.72}, {"text": "bacteria to produce human proteins", "start": 275.04, "duration": 7.68}, {"text": "putting human genes into bacteria lets", "start": 279.0, "duration": 6.6}, {"text": "bacteria create human proteins like", "start": 282.72, "duration": 4.259}, {"text": "insulin", "start": 285.6, "duration": 4.2}, {"text": "we can collect these proteins and use", "start": 286.979, "duration": 5.881}, {"text": "them for medical needs", "start": 289.8, "duration": 6.36}, {"text": "the insertion of genes into crop plants", "start": 292.86, "duration": 6.48}, {"text": "to give them herbicide resistance", "start": 296.16, "duration": 5.34}, {"text": "adding jeans for the herbicide", "start": 299.34, "duration": 5.76}, {"text": "resistance into crops helps them survive", "start": 301.5, "duration": 5.52}, {"text": "herbicides", "start": 305.1, "duration": 5.34}, {"text": "this means better weed control without", "start": 307.02, "duration": 5.52}, {"text": "hurting the plants", "start": 310.44, "duration": 5.34}, {"text": "the insertion of genes into crop plants", "start": 312.54, "duration": 7.32}, {"text": "to give them insect pest resistance", "start": 315.78, "duration": 6.72}, {"text": "adding genes to crops for insect", "start": 319.86, "duration": 5.88}, {"text": "resistance helps plants fight pests", "start": 322.5, "duration": 8.0}, {"text": "without needing lots of chemicals", "start": 325.74, "duration": 4.76}, {"text": "the insertion of genes into crop plants", "start": 331.44, "duration": 7.02}, {"text": "to improve nutritional qualities", "start": 335.1, "duration": 6.42}, {"text": "by adding genes to crops we can boost", "start": 338.46, "duration": 6.06}, {"text": "their nutritional value with things like", "start": 341.52, "duration": 5.76}, {"text": "vitamins and minerals", "start": 344.52, "duration": 6.48}, {"text": "this helps make the crops healthier for", "start": 347.28, "duration": 6.56}, {"text": "people to eat", "start": 351.0, "duration": 2.84}, {"text": "finally let's discuss the advantages and", "start": 354.78, "duration": 6.78}, {"text": "disadvantages of genetically modifying", "start": 358.38, "duration": 8.039}, {"text": "crops including soya Maize and rice", "start": 361.56, "duration": 7.34}, {"text": "the advantages are", "start": 366.419, "duration": 6.181}, {"text": "improved yield genetic modification of", "start": 368.9, "duration": 7.0}, {"text": "crops can make them produce more food to", "start": 372.6, "duration": 6.319}, {"text": "feed more people", "start": 375.9, "duration": 3.019}, {"text": "healthier food some crops can be made", "start": 379.16, "duration": 5.92}, {"text": "with more nutritional content like", "start": 382.44, "duration": 7.28}, {"text": "vitamins to help us stay healthy", "start": 385.08, "duration": 4.64}, {"text": "better for Earth certain genetically", "start": 389.88, "duration": 6.0}, {"text": "modified crops that are more herbicide", "start": 393.0, "duration": 5.94}, {"text": "and pesticide resistant need less", "start": 395.88, "duration": 5.759}, {"text": "harmful chemicals which is better for", "start": 398.94, "duration": 5.06}, {"text": "the planet", "start": 401.639, "duration": 2.361}, {"text": "the disadvantages are", "start": 404.819, "duration": 6.361}, {"text": "loss of biodiversity using a lot of", "start": 407.639, "duration": 7.081}, {"text": "genetically modified crops might mean we", "start": 411.18, "duration": 5.579}, {"text": "don't see as many different types of", "start": 414.72, "duration": 4.94}, {"text": "plants anymore", "start": 416.759, "duration": 2.901}, {"text": "mixing genes genetically modified crops", "start": 420.68, "duration": 7.239}, {"text": "may cross breed with regular ones and", "start": 424.5, "duration": 6.06}, {"text": "spread their changes which could be a", "start": 427.919, "duration": 3.78}, {"text": "problem", "start": 430.56, "duration": 4.199}, {"text": "for example if weeds also become", "start": 431.699, "duration": 6.741}, {"text": "herbicide resistant", "start": 434.759, "duration": 3.681}, {"text": "cost some Farmers might end up needing", "start": 439.02, "duration": 6.179}, {"text": "to buy seeds from just a few big", "start": 442.44, "duration": 7.46}, {"text": "companies which may be expensive", "start": 445.199, "duration": 4.701}, {"text": "so that concludes chapter 21", "start": 451.13